First Read: 03-Mar-26
HJR199 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 HONORING CAPTAIN TED JOHNSON FOR HIS OUTSTANDING SERVICE TO
4 THE RESIDENTS OF MOBILE AND THE MOBILE POLICE DEPARTMENT.
5
6 WHEREAS, with great pride and special pleasure, we
7 highly honor Captain Ted Johnson for his outstanding
8 service, leadership, and dedication to the residents of
9 Mobile and the Mobile Police Department; and
10 WHEREAS, a native of Mobile, Captain Johnson
11 graduated from W.P. Davidson High School before beginning a
12 distinguished career in public safety; he joined the Mobile
13 Police Department in 2006 and was first assigned to the
14 First Precinct as a patrol officer, where he quickly
15 demonstrated a commitment to professionalism and community
16 engagement; and
17 WHEREAS, over the years, he has served in several
18 important roles including motor officer in the Traffic
19 Safety Unit and supervisor in the Second Precinct, where he
20 led felony suspect apprehension efforts, general
21 investigations, and patrol operations; and
22 WHEREAS, Captain Johnson rose through the ranks and
23 was promoted to lieutenant; in that role, he served as the
24 unit commander for the Cyber Intelligence Unit, the
25 Real-Time Information Center, and the Crime Scene Unit;
26 these positions required advanced leadership, investigative
27 expertise, and strategic coordination; and
28 WHEREAS, throughout his career, Captain Johnson has
Page 1

WHEREAS, throughout his career, Captain Johnson has
HJR199 Enrolled
29 been recognized with numerous honors, including the
30 Distinguished Service Award, multiple Excellent Police Duty
31 Awards, Chief's Unit Awards, Chief's Commendations,
32 Life-Saving Awards, and Officer of the Month recognitions;
33 and
34 WHEREAS, Captain Johnson is also deeply committed to
35 education and mentorship; he holds two Bachelor of Arts
36 degrees in Criminal Justice and Russian Language, as well as
37 a Master's Degree in Public Administration from the
38 University of South Alabama, where he currently serves as a
39 part-time faculty member, helping educate and inspire the
40 next generation of leaders; and
41 WHEREAS, beyond his official duties, Captain Johnson
42 has taken a proactive and compassionate approach to
43 addressing homelessness in the Tillman's Corner area in
44 Mobile County; he personally meets with individuals
45 experiencing homelessness to explain local laws and connect
46 them with resources such as identification services, housing
47 assistance, employment opportunities, veteran support, and
48 health care; and
49 WHEREAS, he has also coordinated partnerships with
50 community organizations such as One Meal Mobile, which now
51 uses the precinct as a staging area for weekly meals; as
52 well as First Step Initiative, which assists individuals in
53 obtaining identification, housing, and employment; and
54 WHEREAS, in addition to these outreach efforts,
55 Captain Johnson has worked diligently to improve the
56 cleanliness and safety of the community by enforcing
Page 2

cleanliness and safety of the community by enforcing
HJR199 Enrolled
57 regulations that prevent loitering on state-maintained
58 roadways, reducing litter and hazards in medians and along
59 roadways; and
60 WHEREAS, Captain Ted Johnson's leadership reflects
61 the highest ideals of public service combining enforcement
62 with compassion and safety with community partnership; now
63 therefore,
64 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
65 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Captain Ted Johnson is
66 highly honored for his many professional achievements, and
67 we hereby dedicate this resolution to him with warmest
68 gratitude, admiration, and regard.
